---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '~/components/Breadcrumb.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Comparisons — Dual Scenario Matrix | Kefiw"
  description="Side-by-side calculator scenarios. Run the same deterministic math in parallel and watch the delta bar pick a winner in real time."
  canonical="/comparisons/"
  keywords={['comparison matrix calculators', 'dual scenario', 'side by side decision tool']}
>
  <Breadcrumb crumbs={[{ href: '/', label: 'Home' }, { href: '/comparisons/', label: 'Comparisons' }]} />
  <article class="container-wide py-6">
    <header class="mb-8 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">The Matrix Primitive</p>
      <h1 class="mt-1 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Comparisons</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-slate-700">
        Two scenarios, one form. Each column is an isolated instance of the same tool. The delta bar
        subtracts the live variables and picks a winner.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
        No A/B switching, no "run it again with different numbers." Both paths visible at once.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <a
        href="/comparisons/dual-career-path/"
        class="block rounded-lg border border-cyan-200 bg-white p-5 transition hover:border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-50"
      >
        <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">STAY vs MOVE</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Dual Career Path</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Two Geo Arbitrage forms side-by-side. Price the stay path against the move path. Delta bar
          picks a winner on monthly gain.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">2 scenarios · live delta · ~1 min to set up</div>
      </a>

      <a
        href="/comparisons/role-economics/"
        class="block rounded-lg border border-cyan-200 bg-white p-5 transition hover:border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-50"
      >
        <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">HIRE vs CONTRACT</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Role Economics</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Minimum Viable Rate in two modes — salaried offer vs. contract rate. The honest hourly that matches the W-2 take-home.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">2 scenarios · live delta · ~1 min to set up</div>
      </a>

      <a
        href="/comparisons/platform-arbitrage/"
        class="block rounded-lg border border-cyan-200 bg-white p-5 transition hover:border-cyan-500 hover:bg-cyan-50"
      >
        <div class="text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-cyan-600">GIG-A vs GIG-B</div>
        <div class="mt-1 text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">Platform Arbitrage</div>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Two Gig-Net Floors side-by-side — DoorDash mileage profile vs. Uber routes. Real hourly after IRS depreciation.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">2 scenarios · live delta · ~1 min to set up</div>
      </a>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">How the matrix primitive works</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
        Each column is a namespaced instance of the same tool. They write to separate keys
        (<code class="rounded bg-white px-1 text-xs text-slate-800">field__a</code> and
        <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 text-xs text-slate-800">field__b</code>) in the shared session
        context. The delta bar subscribes to both and re-renders live. No server, no storage off-device.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
